        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "In the bestiary the lion's cubs are born dead and revived on the third day by their father's breath, a figure of Christ's resurrection; this death-and-rebirth aligns the interpretation with the cyclical symbol of death reintegrated as a prelude to renewal."
